        "content": "<p>I'm going to formalize asymptotic series of a function along a filter, with lemmas like uniqueness and \"if there exists an asymptotic series up to each finite order, then they all glue together into 1 asymptotic series\". Is there any standard reference on this topic, or should I start with some definition that fits my use cases and, if needed, generalize later?</p>",
        "id": 398126559,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1698080902
    },
    {
