        "content": "<p>I think analytic number theorists also care about series involving powers of log (or even log  log). E.g. like <a href=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/53dbc2af6df6acd5f9deb00d22f233d2ac9ef59f\">this</a>.</p>",
        "id": 398128459,
        "sender_full_name": "Michael Stoll",
        "timestamp": 1698081766
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Eberl uses a very general notion of asymptotic series in <a href=\"http://cl-informatik.uibk.ac.at/users/meberl//pdfs/real_asymp.pdf\">http://cl-informatik.uibk.ac.at/users/meberl//pdfs/real_asymp.pdf</a></p>",
